As a rule of thumb, use HashMap unless you know you need another Map implementation
okay :simple_smile: , `HashMap` it is

linkedHashmap is really useful for the case where you need the order of input to remain the same. LinkedHashMap is kind of like the PHP associative array. If you built a key=>value set and want to iterate over it to show it in the view, it’ll all be in random order unless you use the linked version
In Android though for a small number for elements ( < 1000) ArrayMap is a good alternative as well
